<br />
I swear I'm laughing so hard right now I have tears coming down my face.  The report is a real nice smear piece on Fox news I'll give it that.  Other than that, the conclusions offered based on the statistics, are completely illegitimate.
<br />

<br />
The didn't not statistically PROVE that Fox News misreports information.  What they proved was that of the people polled, those that believed one of three pieces of disinformation, most of them watched Fox News.
<br />

<br />
Sorry, but any amatuer in statistics will tell you those are NOT the same conclusions.  Try that in a statistics class and the instructor will toss your butt out the door.
<br />

<br />
Also, while how they took the poll was well documented...I saw nothing that answered the questions I asked.  Not even the margin of error.  Those questions are important when analysing statistical data...because if the methods and calculations used to come up with the various numbers is the incorrect formula...well...they product is worthless.  Any amatuer in statistics will tell you that also.
