                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Live from Baghdad is on hbo right now if anyone was up for watching it..heheh <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, I try to be me. I try to be open-minded and even at times, I try to think like the person I may not agree with. Not to go against my own beliefs but to try to atleast understand their reasons in thinking that way. I hate when I do not understand someone or some things, so I atleast try to make an attempt to respect that people stick to their beliefs, even if I don't agree with them.
<br />

<br />
Pride is a good thing, you could swear to me you are the anti-christ and if you stick to that through thick and then. I may think you are a massive freak, but I will respect you for not allowing anyone to tear you down. (ok, maybe not the anti-christ, but I hope you catch my drift)
<br />

<br />
I was at a dinner party at Wyst's house with some fellow EQ'rs. She was reading this forum and showed me Vizier's post from last week. I recall saying outloud that I do not understand him and how it bothered me. 
<br />

<br />
It's just me, I am defensive by nature and if I am to the point I am so defensive I get mean, it is normally something personal or something I feel strongly about. I can't help wanting things to be 'ok'. Granted, I know I cannot fly around feed the hungry, paint everything in pretty colors, plant flowers on bare grounds and fix everything that is broken in the world, even if I want to and I do. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
It takes a lot to admit when I am wrong, sometimes it isn't a case of being wrong but just a matter that noone can be right and noone can be wrong. If it was in the past, it is something we could not change, even if I had the ability to turn back time, I wouldn't want to change the past because it is something for everyone to learn from, good and bad. 
<br />

<br />
I hope one day to see no gaps in leadership worldwide and to see all countries be able to not so much as get along but to agree to respect one another's religions and beliefs and hopefull cut back on war. If it were possible to build an Island for all of the bad people in each country, I'd like to just send them all there so the rest of us can get along with our lives. My family has fought in the war to defend the United States. While I worried about them, I worried about the families and innocent people that were caught in crossfire because of choices the 'bad' people and 'bad' leadership had made causing the U.S. to be at war with their country. 
<br />

<br />
The U.S. has lost many men and women during each war but their lives are not worth any more or any less than those of the innocent women, men and children who were residents of whatever rival country we invaded. It just makes me sad. I'm just a whisper compared to the voices in our country, but I don't think that my voice does not matter. I just cannot do anything to fix what is broken nor could I ever say what I would have done. I do not have all of the facts, I do not know what really is true or false because I am not there, I was not there and I probably never will be there to know, first hand what goes on.
<br />

<br />
I just know that there are too many lives lost because of the conflicts across the world. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, I never kept up with it. How about Canada? I really haven't heard of anything ever happening there. Like, Canada never gets picked on.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" />  In all seriousness, would Canada fall in the place of the U.S. or do they just lay low?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=158777" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ravvenn</a>
<br />
<a href="http://fohguild.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Fires of Heaven</a>
<br />

<br />
